  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I sometimes write longish messages with line/paragraph breaks. When I end a line with an emoji and hit (Shift Enter [in mac]) to start a new line, caret jumps to beginning of current line instead of new line.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCaret shouldn't jump to beginning of current line where Shift Enter was pressed. It should be at the beginning of next line.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nCaret Jumps to the beginning of current line.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to any public channel\r\n- Write a message in the input box with the intention of having multiple lines with line/paragraph break\r\n- Write the first line and end it with any emoji\r\n- Hit Shift Enter (in Mac) or equivalent to go to start next line\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: Desktop Nightly 181008\r\n* Operating System: MacOSX Mojave",
